Philip Herbert Carpenter (6 February 1852 in London – 21 October 1891 in Eton College), MA, D.Sc., FRS, British naturalist and crinoid authority, was the fourth son of Dr. William Benjamin Carpenter.  
He took his own life, by self-administration of chloroform during a bout of temporary insanity caused by chronic insomnia.
